  p.
    You will need to specify whether the off-canvas content is to the left or right &ndash; and also position its respective controller on the same side as the content).
  p.
    You will also need to add an off-canvas control (navicon) for toggling the sidebar. Be sure to set the off-canvas control #[code code data-control_id=""] to point to its respective off-canvas content #[code id=""].
  p.
    It is possible to have more than one off-canvas component. But only one can be activated at a time.

  h3 Controlling the off-canvas content width
  
  p.
    The off-canvas content block will "stretch to fit" the width of whatever content you put inside it (up to 100% width).

  p.
    You can also control the off-canvas content block width in your own stylesheet.
    
  p The following demos operate as off-canvas sidebars at all viewport widths:

  .b--heavy.b--rounded.b--teal-lighten-2.p--16
    
    .off-canvas__ctrl(data-content-id="oc-ex-1").
      #[i.fa.fa-bars(aria-hidden="true")]
    .off-canvas__content.off-canvas__content--left.off-canvas__content--lg.bg--gray-lighten-2#oc-ex-1
      .off-canvas__close.off-canvas__close--right.
        #[i.fa.fa-times(aria-hidden="true")]
      | Example 1: off-canvas sidebar content
    | Demo 1: this off-canvas sidebar is as wide as its content requires.

